goals.question: What is the trend of unemployment rate over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of unemployment rate against year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a general increase or decrease in unemployment rate over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different states?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of unemployment rate against state
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify which states have higher or lower unemployment rates.

goals.question: What is the relationship between unemployment rate and education level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of unemployment rate against education level
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a correlation between education level and unemployment rate.

goals.question: What is the distribution of unemployment rate among different age groups?
goals.visualization: Box plot of unemployment rate against age group
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify which age groups have higher or lower unemployment rates.

goals.question: What is the trend of unemployment rate for different genders?
goals.visualization: Line chart of unemployment rate against year for each gender
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a difference in unemployment rate trend between genders.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['unemployment_rate'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of unemployment rate over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='state', y='unemployment_rate', rot=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different states?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

data = pd.read_csv('unemployment.tsv', sep='\t')
chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['education_level'], data['unemployment_rate'])
    plt.xlabel('Education Level')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the relationship between unemployment rate and education level?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    age_groups = data['age_group'].unique()
    unemployment_rates = [data[data['age_group'] == age]['unemployment_rate'] for age in age_groups]
    
    plt.boxplot(unemployment_rates, labels=age_groups)
    plt.xlabel('Age Group')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate among different age groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_male = data[data['gender'] == 'male']
    data_female = data[data['gender'] == 'female']
    
    plt.plot(data_male['date'], data_male['unemployment_rate'], label='Male')
    plt.plot(data_female['date'], data_female['unemployment_rate'], label='Female')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rate for different genders?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
